        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Alinea exports a JavaScript package which allows your to query content. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "Mqcyu4eHk8PsqVb4mjZwg",
          "type": "ChapterLinkBlock",
          "link": [
            {
              "id": "oHJRFzh1ChngTv3t5jKfe",
              "index": "a0",
              "type": "entry",
              "entry": "28Ng6ZnpyhafrKdGMOO7BUUKP4S",
              "description": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The `alinea init` command links this package by creating an entry in `package.json`. It creates the link slightly differently based on the package manager you use:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "_B5xkuIopw7StPUuUJHz1",
          "type": "CodeVariantsBlock",
          "variants": [
            {
              "id": "3g5p09OtAsBTZLb6JJb5s",
              "index": "a0",
              "type": "Variant",
              "name": "npm & pnpm",
              "language": "tsx",
              "code": "{\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@alinea/content\": \"file:.alinea\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            {
              "id": "yFqMuOpRLVAUm60UiLODj",
              "index": "a1",
              "type": "Variant",
              "name": "yarn",
              "language": "tsx",
              "code": "{\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@alinea/content\": \"link:.alinea\"\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Yarn is different in that it allows `file:` packages but does not symlink them. That means content changes are not available until the next `yarn install`. The other package managers do not support `link:` so we end up with different ways to install. This should not pose a problem but if you ever switch package manager this link will need to be updated."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "alinea": {
    "index": "Zy"
  }
}